{"title_page": "Clara Sosa", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox pageant titleholder\n| name         = Clara Sosa \n| image        = Clara Sosa.png\n| birth_name   = Mar\u00eda Clara Sosa Perdomo\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1991|09|25|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[Asunci\u00f3n]], [[Paraguay]]\n| title        = [[Miss Paraguay|Miss Grand Paraguay 2018]]<br>{{ill|Miss Grand International 2018|es|Miss Grand Internacional 2018|vertical-align=sup}}\n| competitions = [[Miss Model of the World|Miss Model of the World 2015]]<br>(Top 10)<br>[[Miss Expo 2016]]<br>Miss Grand Paraguay 2018<br>(Winner)<br>{{ill|Miss Grand International 2018|es|Miss Grand Internacional 2018|vertical-align=sup}}<br>(Winner)\n| height       = {{height|m=1.75|precision=0}}\n| eye_color    = Brown\n| hair_color   = Black\n| homepage     =\n}}\n\n'''Mar\u00eda Clara Sosa Perdomo''' (born 25 September 1993) is a [[Paraguay]]an model, TV Host and beauty queen who was crowned Miss Grand Paraguay 2018 and was later crowned {{ill|Miss Grand International 2018|es|Miss Grand Internacional 2018|vertical-align=sup}} in [[Yangon]], [[Myanmar]]. She is the first Paraguayan woman to win the Miss Grand International title.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/lifestyle/content/672478/paraguay-s-clara-sosa-faints-after-being-declared-miss-grand-int-l-2018/story/ |title=Paraguay's Clara Sosa faints after being declared Miss Grand Int'l 2018 |publisher=GMA News |last=GMA |first=News |accessdate=26 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/lifestyle/content/672475/paraguay-crowned-miss-grand-int-l-2018-phl-makes-early-exit/story/ |title=Paraguay crowned Miss Grand Int'l 2018; PHL makes early exit |publisher=GMA News |last=GMA |first=News |accessdate=26 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\n\n===Early life===\nSosa was born in the capital of [[Paraguay]], [[Asunci\u00f3n]], and raised in [[San Lorenzo, Paraguay|San Lorenzo]]. She is a model at ON Management and also a host at the morning show ''La ma\u00f1ana de [[Unicanal]]''.\n\n===Pageantry===\nIn 2015, Sosa joined and finished in the Top 20 semifinalist at Miss Model of the World 2015 competition. On 9 June 2018, Sosa was crowned as Miss Grand Paraguay 2018 held its finale night at the Hotel Guarani Theatre. She succeeded outgoing Miss Grand Paraguay 2017, Lia Duarte Ashmore.\n\nAs Miss Grand Paraguay, Sosa won the competition and was crowned {{ill|Miss Grand International 2018|es|Miss Grand Internacional 2018|vertical-align=sup}} was held on 25 October 2018 at One Entertainment Park in [[Yangon]], [[Myanmar]] by outgoing titleholder Miss Grand International 2017, [[Mar\u00eda Jos\u00e9 Lora]] of [[Peru]]. She is the first titleholder from Paraguay and the second from South America.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://beautypageants.indiatimes.com/miss-grand-international/clara-sosa-crowned-miss-grand-paraguay-2018/eventshow/64554640.cms |title=Clara Sosa crowned Miss Grand Paraguay 2018 |publisher=beautypageants.indiatimes.com |accessdate=12 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://peru21.pe/espectaculos/internacional/miss-grand-international-clara-sosa-miss-paraguay-desmayo-ganar-certamen-video-nndc-436627 |title=Clara Sosa, Miss Paraguay, se desmay\u00f3 al ganar el Miss Grand International [VIDEO] |publisher=Peru 21 |accessdate=25 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nDuring the final question for all five was, \"If you were crowned Miss Grand International 2018 tonight and you could choose one country for your first visit to run your first 'Stop the War and Violence Campaign', which country would you choose and what would be your message to them?\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/life/10/26/18/winner-collapses-after-being-named-miss-grand-international-2018 |title=Winner collapses after being named Miss Grand International 2018 |publisher=ABS-CBN News |last=ABS-CBN |first=News |accessdate=26 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theshillongtimes.com/2018/10/26/miss-paraguay-fainted-following-the-announcement-of-miss-grand-international-2018/ |title=Miss Paraguay fainted following the announcement of Miss Grand International 2018 |publisher=The Shillong Times |last=The Shillong |first=Times |accessdate=26 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nClara's winning answer in full:\n\n<blockquote>\n''If I have the honor of being Miss Grand International 2018, I would choose to visit Donald Trump, because the United States of America is an example for other countries. So my first message for him would be to be an example of peace, love, and tolerance.''\n</blockquote>\n\nHer court included [[Meenakshi Chaudhary]] of [[India]] (first runner-up), Nadia Purwoko of [[Indonesia]] (second runner-up), Nicole Col\u00f3n of [[Puerto Rico]] (third runner-up) and Haruka Oda of [[Japan]] (fourth runner-up).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://normannorman.com/2018/10/26/clara-sosa-of-paraguay-wins-miss-grand-international-2018/ |title=Clara Sosa of Paraguay wins Miss Grand International 2018 |publisher=normannorman.com |accessdate=26 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.globalbeauties.com/news/2018/10/25/miss-grand-international-2018-paraguay-wins-and-faints |title=Miss Grand International 2018: Paraguay wins and faints! |publisher=Global Beauties |accessdate=25 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://larepublica.pe/espectaculos/1344635-miss-grand-international-2018-miss-paraguay-clara-sosa-desmayo-enterarse-gano-certamen-belleza-viral-mexico-video |title=Miss Paraguay detiene el Miss Grand International 2018 tras desmayarse en vivo [VIDEO] |publisher=LaRep\u00fablica.pe |accessdate=26 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nSosa ended her reign on October 25, 2019 in [[Caracas]], [[Venezuela]], the host nation of the 2019 Miss Grand International pageant. She eventually crowned [[Valentina Figuera]] of [[Venezuela]] as her successor <ref>{{cite web |url=https://conandaily.com/2019/10/26/venezuelas-valentina-figuera-crowned-miss-grand-international-2019-in-caracas-venezuela/|title=Venezuela\u2019s Valentina Figuera crowned Miss Grand International 2019 in Caracas, Venezuela |publisher=Conan Daily |accessdate=26 October 2019}}</ref>.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.missgrandinternational.com Miss Grand International Official Website]\n*{{Instagram|clarasossa1}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-ach}}\n{{S-bef|before=[[File:Bandera del Departamento de Guair\u00e1.JPG|20px]] Lia Ashmore}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Miss Grand Paraguay \n|years=2018}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[File:Itapflag.PNG|20px]] Milena Rodr\u00edguez}}\n{{S-bef|before={{flagicon|Peru}} Mar\u00eda Jos\u00e9 Lora}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Miss Grand International \n|years=2018}}\n{{S-aft|after={{flagicon|Venezuela}} [[Valentina Figuera]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sosa, Clara}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Paraguayan beauty pageant winners]]\n[[Category:Paraguayan female models]]\n[[Category:People from Asunci\u00f3n]]\n\n\n{{paraguay-bio-stub}}\n{{pageant-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=April 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox pageant titleholder\n| name         = Clara Sosa \n| image        = Clara Sosa.png\n| birth_name   = Mar\u00eda Clara Sosa Perdomo\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1991|09|25|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[Asunci\u00f3n]], [[Paraguay]]\n| title        = [[Miss Paraguay|Miss Grand Paraguay 2018]]<br>{{ill|Miss Grand International 2018|es|Miss Grand Internacional 2018|vertical-align=sup}}\n| competitions = [[Miss Model of the World|Miss Model of the World 2015]]<br>(Top 10)<br>[[Miss Expo 2016]]<br>Miss Grand Paraguay 2018<br>(Winner)<br>{{ill|Miss Grand International 2018|es|Miss Grand Internacional 2018|vertical-align=sup}}<br>(Winner)\n| height       = {{height|m=1.75|precision=0}}\n| eye_color    = Brown\n| hair_color   = Black\n| homepage     =\n}}\n\n'''Mar\u00eda Clara Sosa Perdomo''' (born 25 September 1993) is a [[Paraguay]]an model, TV Host and beauty queen who 